<subSubSection id="DE9853B591995A1BAA732EF216539553" type="description">
<paragraph id="150A448E5A69C22CEFA35654F19E3996" pageNumber="79">
— Cette espece est voisine de 
<taxonomicName id="8EDF6EB23F51F8AAF6E75615E015BF8F" LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:141651" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Ponera" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Ponera cognata Emery" lsidName-HNS="Ponera cognata Emery" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="79" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cognata">P. cognata Sants</taxonomicName>
. Elle s'en distingue toutefois par ses mandibules un peu plus courtes, aux 4 e a 5 e dents anterieures plus grandes (denticulees chez 
<taxonomicName id="BDDCB1EA6CFE5ABE119249C99F6B8354" LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:141651" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Ponera" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Ponera cognata Emery" lsidName-HNS="Ponera cognata Emery" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="79" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cognata">cognata</taxonomicName>
), la tete plus large, l' epistome plus nettement carene, le scape plus court, le tout plus luisant. Dans la figure accompagnant la description de 
<taxonomicName id="796F99CB936CA7039CBEE2ED5CCAAD51" LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:138843" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Ponera" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Ponera lea Santschi" lsidName-HNS="Ponera lea Santschi" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="79" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lea">P. lea</taxonomicName>
, la suture promesonotale de la vue de profil est mal venue, je donne ci-inclus une figure rectificatrice.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
